## Video Editor Job Description
We are searching for people who are not afraid of experimenting. Our candidates should have a basic understanding of the required programs to fulfill the tasks successfully and have a strong desire to develop and grow in this field. Our company is ready to employ people with or without work experience. A key requirement is a fluency in English and an eagerness to be trained. A video editor vacancy is waiting for you!

We will gladly accept creative, quick-thinking, and versatile people who are ready to try their hand at making up video content. With our support and help, you will learn how to create high-quality video content and improve your skills in practice. You will create promotional videos for different companies and videos for social networks, namely YouTube, Facebook, Instagram, etc. Has a video editor vacancy caught your eye? Go for it!## Video Editor Job Responsibilities:
* manage technical aspects of video recording;
* assembling the best material into a finished video product;
* montage;
* work with graphics, transitions, and special effects;
* color correction;
* sound and imagine synchronization;
* design the video with titles, musical score, and captions.
## Required programs for a Video Editor to work with:
* **Adobe Premiere Pro -** this application provides professional video editing and contains a wide variety of effects and filters. It is possible to make the video montage in real-time.
* **Sony Vegas Pro -** it has in-built special effects and crossfades that can be adjusted. It is possible to create and edit a colorful volume animation in 3D.
* **Adobe After Effects -** this application is suitable for footage editing and the creation of motion graphics, animations, and various special effects. With the help of After Effects, you will be able to create static 3D images such as logotypes, typography, and scenes.
Record [a video interview](/videointerview) and tell us about your skills and knowledge.

## About us
RemotEmployees – outstaffing company involved in searching for remote workers for employment in major foreign projects.
## Our expectations from Motion Designer
* Confident or basic knowledge of After Effects, Adobe Premiere, Photoshop, and Illustrator 2D;
* Attentiveness and a systematic approach for meeting the challenges;
* Basic 3D editor knowledge will be an advantage;
* Pursuit to grow and develop in the direction of motion design;
* Ability to establish priorities and strictly meet customer’s requirements;
* Ability to define a clear attitude and solution concerning design;
* Distinct insight into video editing, storyboarding, and engagement with a camera.
## Basic tasks of Motion Designer
* Creation of animated visualizations;
* Creation and installation of advertising and presentation videos;
* Structure development, dynamic shot creation, and work with color circle;
* Communication with customers and fulfilling tasks in English
\* Be ready to complete a test task!
## We offer:
* Full-time;
* Five-day, 8-hour work schedule;
* On-the-job training and support for beginners (Junior/ Middle);
* Remote employment and flexible working hours
If you are not sure about your experience in **motion design**, but you are eager to learn and develop your skills, we are also ready to consider you for this position!
Just send us your CV and a [short video story](/videointerview) about yourself, and we will send you an offer within one week!
## Ready to Join?
Do not miss the chance to apply for the vacancy of a motion designer. Improve your skills and expand your experience by working on major international projects worldwide! Don’t hesitate- contact us right now!

## Who are we looking for in the position of Interior designer?
Do you want to work on foreign projects? We have been cooperating with customers from Europe and the USA for 2.5 years. 
At the moment, we have a vacancy for **Interior Designer.** If you have ever worked in such programs as Photoshop, CorelDraw, 3Ds Max, Adobe Illustrator, ArchiCad or AutoCAD or VRay, and also like to decorate interiors then leave your contact details on our website.
We also have a vacancy for an **assistant interior designer,** even without work experience. We engage people for internships with foreign customers. If you do not have an architectural education but have finished the courses and are looking for your first job, then you are welcome to send us your CV.
## What do we expect from an interior designer?
It will be an advantage for you if:
* you already have work experience and a portfolio;
* you know the market for finishing materials, furniture, etc.;
* you developed design elements by yourself;
* you are not afraid of new projects;
* you are communicative and ready to listen to the client;
* you know the basics of ergonomics;
* you love your job and have a desire to develop in your sphere.
If you are a beginner interior designer, interested in design and want to try yourself in this profession, you can get an internship as an interior designer or get the position of an assistant interior designer even without work experience.

We are looking for both professionals and beginners to work as interior designers remotely. Your diligence and desire to develop are important to us.
Welcome to Remote Employees! Leave a request or record [a video interview](/videointerview) and we will contact you soon!
